article.headline: Gardner-Webb 64, Winthrop 49
article.story: ROCK HILL, S.C. -- Aaron Linn scored 13 points as Gardner-Webb defeated Winthrop 64-49 on Wednesday night. Linn also finished with six rebounds, two blocks and two steals for the Runnin' Bulldogs (7-9, 3-3 Big South Conference). Grayson Flittner contributed 10 points, six rebounds and six assists. Gardner-Webb used a 15-0 run to end the first half, and held a 39-23 lead at the break. The Runnin' Bulldogs maintained their lead throughout the second half and never led by less than 14 points. The Eagles (3-12, 2-4) were paced by Mantoris Robinson, who scored 16 points on 8 of 10 shooting. Charles Corbin chipped in with 14 points and five rebounds. Winthrop outscored the Runnin' Bulldogs in the paint 34-18, but was outrebounded 44-31. The Eagles shot 35 percent from the field (21-for-60), and made only one of their 15 3-point attempts (6.7 percent).
